HOW TO INSTALL ELSI
===================

#########################################################################
A) Install from zero: if you do not have any part of the ELSI package 
   installed before, you may choose this way to build everything for you.
#########################################################################

1) Variables in the file "make.sys" control the process of installation.
   Edit this file to match your platform/environment.

1.1) GLOBAL
   Set compilers, archive tools, and installation path of linear algebra
   library, which will be used during the whole installation.

1.2) ELSI
   Set Fortran compiler flags.

1.3) ELPA
   Set compiler flags, choose ELPA2 kernels, switch on/off OpenMP.

1.4) libOMM
   Set Fortran compiler flags.

1.5) PEXSI
   Set compiler flags and installation paths of ParMetis/SuperLU_DIST.

1.6) LINK
   Since you do not have ELPA, libOMM, or PEXSI installed, please use
   the default settings here.

2) Make sure your "make.sys" is correctly configured.

   Run "make -f Makefile.elsi" to build ELPA, libOMM, PEXSI, and the
   ELSI interface.

   Run "make -j -f Makefile.elsi" to build ELSI in parallel.

3) To install ELSI as a library, run "make -f Makefile.elsi install".

4) Run "make -f Makefile.elsi check" to perform the regression test.
   (not yet functional)

#######################################################################
B) If you already have some libraries of ELSI installed, you may choose
   to just build what you need.
#######################################################################

   E.g. you have ELPA on your system. You still need to build libOMM, 
   PEXSI, and the ELSI interface. The process of installation could be 
   as follows:

1) Edit the file "make.sys".

1.1) LINK
   Set the directory and include/lib path of ELPA. Use the default
   settings for libOMM and PEXSI.

1.2) GLOBAL & ELSI & libOMM & PEXSI
   Same as described in A).

1.3) ELPA
   Do nothing.

2) Make sure your "make.sys" is correctly configured.

   Run "make -f Makefile.elsi {omm|pexsi|elsi}" to build OMM, PEXSI, 
   and the ELSI interface one by one.

3) To install ELSI as a library, run "make -f Makefile.elsi install".

4) Run "make -f Makefile.elsi check" to perform the regression test.
   (not yet functional)
